WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.081 --> 00:00:03.831
(dramatic music)

00:00:11.730 --> 00:00:15.120
- When someone asks if
they're proportioned

00:00:15.120 --> 00:00:18.680
correctly for X3 or if

00:00:18.680 --> 00:00:20.730
they're too big or too small

00:00:20.730 --> 00:00:22.130
or something like that.

00:00:22.130 --> 00:00:24.900
Andre Drummond is an NBA player,

00:00:24.900 --> 00:00:27.000
he's actually a hall of famer NBA player,

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:28.700
he plays for The Detroit Pistons.

00:00:28.700 --> 00:00:31.750
He has no trouble doing
any of the movements,

00:00:31.750 --> 00:00:33.780
obviously he has very wide shoulders

00:00:33.780 --> 00:00:36.380
there's also seven NFL players

00:00:36.380 --> 00:00:38.440
that are using X3 and
the numbers are growing

00:00:38.440 --> 00:00:39.570
all the time.

00:00:39.570 --> 00:00:42.120
Recently a lot of NFL
players have been talking

00:00:42.120 --> 00:00:45.120
about X3 and they've been
switching completely over

00:00:45.120 --> 00:00:47.763
so they're dropping weights and using X3.

00:00:49.240 --> 00:00:50.440
Just a little side note,

00:00:50.440 --> 00:00:52.310
working with athletes is great because

00:00:52.310 --> 00:00:54.890
they don't care how much
they bench of squat.

00:00:54.890 --> 00:00:56.850
They're paid to perform on the field,

00:00:56.850 --> 00:00:58.960
so they're gonna do whatever is best,

00:00:58.960 --> 00:01:03.960
which is a great segway into
talking about bar width.

00:01:05.360 --> 00:01:07.170
So another question we get is

00:01:07.170 --> 00:01:09.060
why isn't the bar wider?

00:01:09.060 --> 00:01:12.300
I like to do wide grip bench press.

00:01:12.300 --> 00:01:15.870
So the reason people like
wide grip bench press

00:01:15.870 --> 00:01:19.590
is because it's easier, or
you can handle more weight.

00:01:19.590 --> 00:01:22.360
Because the distance the arm has to travel

00:01:22.360 --> 00:01:24.900
when it's matched with the shoulders

00:01:24.900 --> 00:01:29.150
is a lot longer than if you grab out here

00:01:29.150 --> 00:01:30.460
this is a shorter distance.

00:01:30.460 --> 00:01:34.840
Now that's okay if you're
doing like a feat of strength

00:01:35.930 --> 00:01:38.240
if you're in a bench press competition,

00:01:38.240 --> 00:01:40.450
a wide grip is a better idea,

00:01:40.450 --> 00:01:43.900
because you're gonna be
able to handle more force.

00:01:43.900 --> 00:01:48.150
But really a wide grip is great for

00:01:48.150 --> 00:01:50.510
talking about your bench press.

00:01:50.510 --> 00:01:52.660
So like a lot of the guys on the internet,

00:01:52.660 --> 00:01:55.253
they like bragging about
how much they bench,

00:01:56.580 --> 00:01:59.460
but that doesn't mean you're stronger.

00:01:59.460 --> 00:02:01.960
So X3 is designed to get you stronger

00:02:01.960 --> 00:02:05.460
so just in a simple illustration.

00:02:05.460 --> 00:02:08.220
Where is the pectoral if I put my arm

00:02:08.220 --> 00:02:10.230
out here like I'm doing a wide grip,

00:02:10.230 --> 00:02:12.420
is the pectoral fully
contracted right here?

00:02:12.420 --> 00:02:14.953
No, its fully contracted right here.

00:02:16.210 --> 00:02:18.640
So you're actually not
stimulating the muscles

00:02:18.640 --> 00:02:20.840
you're trying to stimulate
when you do wide grip.

00:02:20.840 --> 00:02:22.740
So wide grip is really just great

00:02:22.740 --> 00:02:25.290
if you wanna talk about your bench press,

00:02:25.290 --> 00:02:26.920
not actually get stronger.

00:02:26.920 --> 00:02:30.140
X3 is for getting stronger.

00:02:30.140 --> 00:02:32.760
So you want a much more narrow grip

00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:35.260
so you can squeeze those pectorals,

00:02:35.260 --> 00:02:38.900
and stimulate what you're
intending to stimulate

00:02:38.900 --> 00:02:41.373
when doing the contraction.

